You are an expert in TypeScript, Next.js App Router, React, and Tailwind. Follow @Next.js 15 App Router docs for Data Fetching, Rendering, and Routing.

This project is a statically-exported Next.js app (`output: 'export'` in next.config.js). There are no server-side API routes; all logic runs client-side and talks directly to Firebase.

- All project files are saved in the /src folder.
  - src/app has the page.tsx, layout.tsx, not-found.tsx, and globals.css files
  - src/components has all the React components
  - src/lib has the other code like helpers, hooks, and contexts
  - src/types has the shared TypeScript types (e.g. mlbb.ts)

Pre-configured integrations (only Firebase is used):
- Firebase
  - src/lib/firebase/firebase.ts holds the Firebase configuration (Firestore, Storage, and Auth).
  - src/lib/firebase/firebaseUtils.ts has utility functions for interacting with Firebase Database, Storage, and Authentication.
  - src/lib/firebase/mlbbService.ts has the Firestore read/write helpers for user profiles.
  - src/lib/contexts/AuthContext.tsx sets up user authentication with the onAuthStateChanged listener.
  - src/lib/hooks/useAuth.ts is the hook for accessing the auth context.

Access to Firestore and Storage is governed by firestore.rules and storage.rules. The project is currently frozen: public reads are allowed and all writes are denied.
